PHYSICAL THERAPY IS ABOUT OPTIMIZING MOVEMENT to help people return to doing what they LOVE (for us gaming for 10 hours) without PAIN. It's so often that we are thought of specialist masseuses who ice, heat and apply electrical stimulation as a way to reduce pain. This is far from what we do and what we're capable of. . . As movement specialist we help to identify the contributing "MOVEMENT IMPAIRMENTS" which limit you from playing CS:GO for 10 hours, being able to participate in a crossfit WOD, getting on the mat for some sparring, playing 18 holes of golf. Typically, these fall into THREE major categories which we identify through our assessments and observation of your movements: **1** Mobility - Do you have muscles or joints that are short/stiff limiting the your movement? **2** Power/Strength - Is there an imbalance of muscles increasing stress at your joints? **3** Motor Coordination - Are you able to use the right muscles in the right order for the movements you are performing throughout they day? . . So don't be afraid to seek us out so we can help you MOVE better, so you can GAME better.

Sushi Donuts. A tantalizing social media find. There was no way we'd go to SoCal without trying this alluring dish -- sushi in donut form! Project Poke, a spot located in an average shopping center, was relatively small and had quite a line. Long enough for us to decide which donuts we wanted to order, while not standing around for a painstakingly long time. We ordered the salmon and combo. To my disappointment, they're all pre-made. But I suppose that's understandable due to their social media fame aka demand is high. Despite this, the sushi donuts were great. Just like sushi rolls yet not at the same time. It was strange. I definitely recommend getting the seaweed underneath the donut or you could be in for quite a mess - like when you squeeze sushi too hard with your chopsticks and it falls apart (keyword: you). Either way, it was a colorful treat. (I mean, aren't they gorgeous?!) Luckily, there's a spot in Houston now where we can order some, if we so crave. #RealMadridLA #LostInLA #dineLA #eatmunchies

What's ur plan? #ilivelifeill #repost @goodlife . . . . . Having big dreams is great until you get so caught up inside of them that you forget to actually execute. Making plans and working out a strategy to make it happen is what you need to be doing. You want the freedom money gives you, the cars, the travels, the things you've always dreamed of, then make a plan and go get them. Sit down, grab a piece of paper and a pen and write down your goals and your ideas. Figure out how you're going to make your dreams come true and hustle every single day until it happens. There are no days off when you have big dreams, you need to put in the work if you want it all to happen. It all starts in your head, you are the master of your decisions and your actions. Train your brain to have a good work ethic and good habits, stop making excuses and go get it. I don't dream of the Porsche 918 anymore, I plan on getting it. I actually told my boy @briangoldphd (the owner) that I'd come back to him one day with an offer on his car. Man I love it, it has got to be one of the most gorgeous cars ever made, and I'll do whatever it takes to call it mine one day. Along with all the things I dream of owning and doing, nothing and nobody will ever stop me from reaching my destination, or affect my process. - F üëäüèª #Goodlife  #porsche #918 #quote #quotes #work #inspiration #entrepreneur #entrepreneurship #mtl #montreal #514 #success #montrealer #LA #losangeles #hypercar #porsche918 #dreamcar #dreamchaser #morelife

One sure way to get me to order a dessert at your restaurant is to create something I haven't seen before.  But if you're going to do that make sure the picture you use to advertise it matches what arrives on the plate.  This is the Nutella Calzone.  I know, it already sounds awesome.  And it almost was.  The picture advertising this cool dessert from @800degreespizza says the calzone will come with mixed fruit, Nutella, chocolate and a scoop of gelato (points to them for letting you pick the flavor) on top.  The picture though shows the mixed fruit (strawberries & blueberries) outside the calzone spread around on the chocolate lines that cover the plate.  When the dessert was presented to me the fruit was nowhere to be found.  As I'm not keen on mixing fruit with Nutella I was grateful for the accidental omission.  However, when I started eating the calzone I noticed a hint of fruit in each bite and upon closer inspection realized the fruit was inside the calzone which tempered my enthusiasm for this dessert immensely.  Blueberries are fine but mixing them with Nutella did neither flavor any favors.  Having fruit on the outside at least allows the eater to control how much, if any, fruit you want in each bite.  But baking it in means you have to dig and search for any fruit you don't want in each bite.  I'd like to go back and give this another shot and make sure to order it without fruit because the crust was soft and chewy and the Nutella was nice and warm and it would make for a tasty treat all by themselves.  Okay, strawberries, you can jump in occasionally but blueberries - you are not invited to the next eat date. #frankeatsfood #foodie #foodporn #calzone #nutella #dessert #800degreespizza #gelato #chocolate #delicious #yummy #losangeles

Songkran is the Thai New Year and it's also a near year celebrated in both Laos and Cambodia! It's a time when we come together with our families and splash ourselves with some water to cleanse and welcome the goodness which awaits us in the new year. We normally go out to the temple but Dad wasn't feeling the big adventure so we kept it low key and festive from the enclaves of our living room.  I'm not sure if my parents ever played with water guns before but they were sure pros today!  Happy Songkran! Happy Thai New Year! . . . . .  So thankful that the clan are such sports. They only let me punch out about 5 photos and Dad was already calling out for his afternoon nap. . . . . .

For me inspiration is almost never planned and it usually comes in sporadic moments that you couldn't have put together yourself. Somehow this cocktail of events led to this moment that I have to make note of immediately before it's gone. Almost like a shooting star if I don't catch its brilliance in that very moment it can be lost in a blink. I believe these moments that awaken us in ways that almost no one else understands are the moments that our creator whispers to the very depths of our gifts that been planted deep inside our soul. It's a kindle of a flame that can only be felt and is unseen. The only visible evidence of this inspiration is when we put our hands to work. It's our willingness to execute and manifest our God given talents to give to the world so we can show them in a tangible form that which inspires us. Transformation Tuesday coming to you from LA this week! On the right is 2 years ago in Vegas. This was in the Hollywood hills today. (Nearly) 8 stone lighter than last time. I would normally be in leggings and jumper or long smocks. Flat shoes to save blisters and wouldn't have dreamt of wearing wedges while walking. Even had my legs out again. They have not seen the sun for decades üòÇ Today I climbed 195 steps to reach the top of the Hollywood hills to pose for this photo. Last time I didn't do it. I sat at the bottom and waited for everyone as I was too embarrassed to get halfway and have to pause and be out of breath and I was too lazy. Today I did it! I climbed it with everyone else. Anyone struggling right now I wished I had someone to tell me the last 20 years to keep going to be that person and to be fitter happier and healthier. KEEP GOING! Here is Pac on set..the people that he is with here are Frank Alexanders family members from Chicago. The little boy in the middle is Franks nephew, who is a rapper now named Julius something...cant recall the full name. The girl in the wheelchair is Franks niece. The other two are also Franks family members. This was in June of '96 when Pac invited Franks family from Chicago to come and spend time with Pac in LA. Franks niece was a parapalegic from a car accident a few yrs prior. She was part of Make A Wish Foundation. The MAWF is something for kids who would like to meet a celebrity and spend time with them. Janet Jackson was suppose to meet her but Janet only promised an hour of her "busy" time to spend with Franks niece. When Pac heard that he immediately told Frank "Eff Janet, bring them here and I will spend the entire week with them". Lets stop for a sec...who does that? We're talking about the biggest rap star in 1996 with a jam packed schedule stops his time for his close friend/bodyguards family bc Pac knew it would make them so happy. No big named rapper today would ever do that... Franks nieces name was Leveeka, I think. She even featured on one of Pacs unreleased tracks with Tha Outlawz. Leevka, if youre out there somewhere...please holler at me. Kate Braverman's Frantic Transmissions to and from Los Angeles. üôèüèª These quotes: "We meet at the Santa Monica pier at irregular intervals, a birth, a death, a daughter's medical-school graduation, or a chance airline confusion. Our forty-year friendships are secondary. Memory is not static. It's in flux, mutating through time and accumulation. There's a give, the way cliffs above the Pacific Coast Highway shed themselves across decades. We are left with too few artifacts. Proof is elusive. Sea breezes embrace seductive star jasmine while Santa Anas blow salt through the dusk like stray bullets. But our lives are not fictions. We meet and remember. We bear witness for one another. This is our central function." ‚ú®"Los Angeles, the destination city, capital of film and media, did not yet exist. This was an era before the image became holy and ineffable. Our Los Angeles was where you went after divorce or scandal, bankruptcy, foreclosure, imminent starvation, bad health, and personal exile. There was nothing glamorous about it. One came from calamity, lured by the promise of a winter in permanent remission where you could have asthma and heart attacks with minimal heating bill." ‚ú®"Nature was what happened when you walked out your door. Or was it? We were denied maples and oaks, the deciduous trees that obeyed the European natural order of budding, spring, summer, and incomprehensible illumination of an autumn of leaves turning yellow and red, burgundy and orange before the ordained winter. Our nature was what pushed up on its own accord from slats in fences and cracks in alleys, the blaze of crimson and gold canna, the sticky white and pink oleander, sudden eruptions of agapanthus and jacaranda. Our nature was innumerable varieties of palm trees that were not deciduous but unrepentantly vertical, with pitiful daggers of unpredictable partial shade. Holden Caulfield would have stabbed himself."
